{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9b6350ae-ae6a-43a1-beec-75373e67488b","content":"Use `Assert.ThrowsException` (MSTest) or `Assert.Throws` (xUnit/NUnit) instead:\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()\n{\n    var service = new UserService();\n\n    var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n        () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n\n    Assert.AreEqual(\"email\", ex.ParamName); // bonus: verify details\n}\n```\n\n**Why switch:**\n- `[ExpectedException]` passes if *any* line throws, masking bugs (e.g., the constructor could throw instead of `CreateUser`)\n- `Assert.ThrowsException` pinpoints the exact call and lets you inspect the exception","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ed03f5b2-e125-4af3-868c-f54f205fc7e0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about modernizing a C# test that uses the `[ExpectedException]` attribute. This is a general knowledge question — no need to explore the codebase.","outputTokens":240,"requestId":"4812:3395C8:826583:963687:69FBEA05"},"id":"5892e35c-4bcf-4aff-a3df-d48f6461f21b","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:25:30.783Z","parentId":"0968bcd7-68c7-4279-8653-aa03c259b7e2"}
